<tr style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->
<td style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Our modules are based on distance learning using a blend of print, audio and video, and collaborative opportunities through forums (moodle) and Elluminate. &nbsp;We need to decide how much reading we can direct students to do online, when the majority is currently in print. Health and social care is a constantly changing landscape not least with every new government bringing in rafts of new policy. We are really stuck when this is in our print resources, but we know students prefer to read print. I&rsquo;d like to try out ways of making the online material as accessible and brief as possible.</td>
