                    <item>
              <title>Sue Watling Cloud for OLDs MOOC</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6837</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6837</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>One of the challenges of working online is the proliferation of places to work in. It is early days on the OLDs MOOC but already there is additional email traffic and new online places to explore (Cloudworks, Google Groups, Bibsomony etc). This in itself is an interesting experience. Many of them are strange and digital confidence directly relates to existing experience &ndash; in particular with navigating around social networking platforms - so for participants new to working online this in itself may pose a barrier.</p>
<p>When it comes to online presence, I prefer less to more &ndash; like single sign-on in reverse &ndash; one post which appears in multiple places. I would be interested to know how other people manage their online lives. &nbsp;</p>]]></description>
