                    <item>
              <title>EOR: Example uses of the Ecology of Resources Design Framework</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6654</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6654</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>Skim through the presentations (embedded below) to get a feel for how the EoR design framework has been used in:</p>
<ul>
<li>design of support for better connecting primary school and home numeracy learning using tablet PCs.</li>
<li>co-design of technology-enhanced learning about sustainability with teenagers.</li>
<li>co-design of BYOD support for self-managed learning field trips with teenagers.</li>
<li>workshops with teachers designing technology-enhanced participatory science inquiry activities for secondary &amp; primary school.</li>
<li>participatory design of an Android app for foreign language vocabulary learning with self-directed adult learners.</li>
</ul>
<div>For a more detailed description of the framework and worked examples see the <a href="http://eorframework.pbworks.com/w/page/3777765/FrontPage" target="_blank">EoR Design Framework &amp; Models Wiki</a>.</div>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->These examples are used with&nbsp;<a style="color: #003366;" href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloudscape/view/2455">EoR Phase 1 Cloudscape</a></p>
<div>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Go to&nbsp;<a style="color: #003366;" href="http://www.olds.ac.uk/the-course/inquire">OLDSMOOC-Week2-Web</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a style="color: #003366;" href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloudscape/view/2460">OLDSMOOC-Week2-on-Cloudworks</a></p>
<p>You can leave feedback on any activity in the discussion around the corresponding cloud and/or using the&nbsp;<a style="color: #003366;" href="http://www.olds.ac.uk/feedback" target="_blank">feedback form</a>.</p>
</div>
<p><a style="color: #003366;" rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/uk/deed.en_GB"><img style="border-style: none;" src="http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-sa/2.0/uk/88x31.png" alt="Creative Commons Licence" /></a><br />This work&nbsp;is licensed&nbsp;under a&nbsp;<a style="color: #003366;" rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/uk/deed.en_GB">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 2.0 UK: England &amp; Wales License</a>.</p>]]></description>
